# Phase 2 — Supabase + Google OAuth Setup

**Windsurf Prompt:**
> "Set up Supabase Auth with Google OAuth in Next.js 14 App Router. Create `lib/supabase/client.ts` and `lib/supabase/server.ts` using `@supabase/ssr`. Add middleware.ts that protects `/dashboard` and redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`. Use environment variables."

**Manual Steps:**
1. Go to [supabase.com](https://supabase.com) → New Project
2. Dashboard → Auth → Providers → Enable **Google**
3. Go to [console.cloud.google.com](https://console.cloud.google.com) → Create Project → Enable **Google OAuth 2.0** → Copy Client ID + Secret into Supabase
4. Create `.env.local`:
```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_url
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret
```

**Supabase SQL to run:**
```sql
create table public.users (
  id uuid references auth.users primary key,
  email text, full_name text, avatar_url text,
  created_at timestamp default now()
);
alter table users enable row level security;
create policy "Users see own data" on users for all using (auth.uid() = id);
```

